data.text:
The thing is, based on Ranpo's previous statements If we fought the Port Mafia head-on, people would die, [now that we've failed to apprehend the ability user who created the virus] we're out of chips to bargain with the Port Mafia. Tanizaki is in danger., I'm fairly sure assassinating the pm boss was not the task the ada assigned Tanizaki. Which means Tanizaki literally goes for the murder option of his own accord as soon as he's left unsupervised.

Do you ever think about how the tiniest change of action can have irreversible repercussions over the course of the entire plot. Like for example if Akutagawa had been there in chapter 47 he wouldn't have been able to support Atsushi in his fight against Fukuchi and Fukuchi would have conquered the whole world and they would all be dead just because seeing Atsushi catch a bullet with his teeth would have killed Akutagawa on the spot

Look I know I'm supposed to side with the good guys and everything but I'm going to be honest with you here pal: when Dostoyevsky successfully shot Dazai I cheered
